The Text Encoding Initiative (TEI) is both a community of practise of text-based digital humanities practitioners and a set of guidelines produced by them for encoding digital texts in XML. Pages in this category relate in some way to use of the TEI guidelines

See [[w:Text Encoding Initiative|Text Encoding Initiative]].

