oc/2006/2006canlii40975/2006canlii40975.html 2006 CanLII 40975] (ONCA) || 8 years || |- | R. v. Turtle||[http://www.canlii.org/en/mb/mbca/doc/2006/2006mbca148/2006mbca148.html 2006 MBCA 148 ] || 42 months || residence present; no violence used |- | R. v. Vincent|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/bc/bcca/doc/2006/2006bcca135/2006bcca135.html 2006 BCCA 135] || 9 months || followed victim into condo suite; pretended to be police; ran away when asked for search warrant |- |R. v. Carvalho|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/on/onca/doc/2006/2006canlii12959/2006canlii12959.html 2006 CanLII 12959 (ON C.A.)] || 5 years || break into residence at night while owner sleeping; then broke into back shed; very long record |- |R. v. Best ||[http://canlii.ca/t/1l8g6 2005 NSSC 199] ||12 years || aggravated assault with B&E; lengthy non-violent record |- |R. v. Desrochers|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/mb/mbca/doc/2005/2005mbca115/2005mbca115.html 2005 MBCA 115] ||15 months || 2 residential break-ins; ran away; record was lengthy with property offences; breaches |- |R. v. Pinch || [http://www.canlii.org/en/ns/nssc/doc/2005/2005nssc122/2005nssc122.html 2005 NSSC 122]|| 4 years|| |- | R. v. Pakoo|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/mb/mbca/doc/2004/2004mbca157/2004mbca157.html 2004 MBCA 157] || 5 years || |- |R. v. Sharphead||[http://www.canlii.org/en/ab/abca/doc/2004/2004abca338/2004abca338.html 2004 ABCA 338 ] || 3 years || broke into victim's home; committed aggravated assault with knife; no prior record |- |R. v. MacKenzie || [http://www.canlii.org/en/ns/nsca/doc/2004/2004nsca117/2004nsca117.html 2004 NSCA 68] ||2 years || 28 convictions on record; 10 for property offences |- |R. v. Johnson|| [http://canlii.ca/t/1hzqf 2004 ABCA 308] || 2.5 years || break in residence while intoxicated, in bedroom of victim; woke her up, put hand on throat causing bruises |- | R. v. Parlee|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/nb/nbca/doc/2002/2002nbca21/2002nbca21.html 2002 NBCA 21] ||2 years less a day||knocked on door; resident called police; arrested with drill |- |R. v. Howard|| [http://www.canlii.org/en/nb/nbqb/doc/1991/1991canlii2648/1991canlii2648.html 1991 CanLII 2648 (NB Q.B.)] ||18 months || enters house through basement window; flees, long criminal record |}
